{"id": 8101, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "HL", "paper": "1", "year": "2020", "session": "20N", "subtopic": "20-1-types-of-organic-reactions", "title": "20N.1.HL.TZ0.35", "topic_id": "20", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Which is the electrophile in the nitration of benzene?</span></p>\n<p>A.  <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>HNO</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math></p>\n<p>B.  <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><msub><mi>NO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo></msup></math></p>\n<p>C.  <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><msub><mi>NO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo></msup></math></p>\n<p>D.  <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>+</mo></msup></math></p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>B</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>The vast majority selected the nitronium ion as the electrophile in the nitration of benzene.</p>\n</div>"}